    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA141-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu poruḷ kaṭaikkūṭṭiya neñciṟkut talaivaṉ collic celavu aḻuṅkiyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is how HE prevented going by speaking to [his] heart that coveted wealth.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA141">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            iruñcem muṭiya koṭuṅkavuṭ kayavāy</l>
<l>            māri yāṉaiyiṉ maruṅku ṟīṇṭip</l>
<l>            poriyarai ñemirnta puḻaṟkāyk koṉṟai</l>
<l>            nīṭiya caṭaiyō ṭāṭā mēṉik</l>
<l>            kuṉṟuṟai tavaciyar pōlap palavuṭa </l>
<l>            ṉeṉṟūḻ nīḷiṭaip poṟpat tōṉṟu</l>
<l>            maruñcura meḷiyamaṉ ṉiṉakkē paruntupaṭap</l>
<l>            pāṇṭiloṭu poruta palpiṇart taṭakkai</l>
<l>            yēntukōṭ ṭiyāṉai yicaiveṅ kiḷḷi</l>
<l>            vampaṇi yuyarkoṭi yampar cūḻnta </l>
<l>            varicilan teḷḷaṟa laṉṉavivaḷ</l>
<l>            viriyoli kūntal viṭṭamai kalaṉē.</l>
            </lg>
       <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>To you the difficult deserts [may be] easy,</l>
<l rend="indent">where the Laburnum trees with hollow unripe fruits crushed</l>
<l rend="indent3">on the parched trunk,</l>
<l rend="indent2">rubbing(?) the stomach of the cloud[-coloured] elephant</l>
<l rend="indent2">with deep mouth [and] bent cheek on [its] big red head,</l>
<l rend="indent">appear beautifully on the long way in the sun,</l>
<l rend="indent2">many together, like ascetics dwelling in the hills,</l>
<l rend="indent2">bodies motionless, with long-grown matted locks.</l>
<l>I won't let go completely<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">viṭṭ amaikalaṉ</term>: here we can understand <term xml:lang="ta">amai</term> as auxiliary (see above) or quite literally: "I won’t be content, having let go of ...". If we accept the situation evoked by the <term xml:lang="ta">kiḷavi</term>, that is, HE telling his heart that he will not go, the former solution would make it a kind of solemn declaration of intent.</note> of the broadly sprouting tresses</l>
<l rend="indent">of her who [is] like the clear water of the Aricil river</l>
<l rend="indent2">that surrounded Ampar, with high flags for a fresh decoration,</l>
<l rend="indent2">[belonging to] Kiḷḷi, desirous of fame, with high-tusked elephants</l>
<l rend="indent3">with broad trunks with many rough spots that dashed against</l>
<l rend="indent4">chariots(?)<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">pāṇṭiloṭu</term> "with circles" is explained by T.V.G. as the wheels that are pars pro toto for the chariots to which the elephant are attached.</note></l>
<l rend="indent3">so that kites were coming (to take the prey).</l>
        </lg>
         </div>
